{
  "texts": [
    "It is their decision not to publish deeper levels of geographical granularity-but they could do so as a matter of fact.",
    "For the construction of MrP projections, cell-level predictions are generated.",
    "These cells can be privacy-violating, as the following example illustrates.",
    "There are around 40 By simple average, this results in 3 individuals per cell-and while the distribution of individuals across cells is far from uniform, there is no doubt at least some of these cells will contain a single individual.",
    "At some stage in the MrP process, a prediction is made and stored on a computer for a single individual."
  ]
}